Full_Description:
Client Services Specialist - after-sales Internet customer service-related software embedded in the system - based in Bangkok, work from home (sometimes need to go to the office)

Working hours: Shift system, 8:00-17:00/9:00-18:00/13:00-22:00, 8 hours per day, 2 days off per week

Employment Model: Local Recruitment

Start Date: Urgent Recruitment, Join as Soon as Possible

Contract Form: Local EOR third-party signing

Background

1. IT or software system customer service experience

2.Hotel procurement staff, hotel IT maintenance personnel

Directly responsible for software system configuration, remote troubleshooting, version updates, and daily operation and maintenance, ensuring the smooth operation of the software system, is a typical system embedded customer service job. Provide customers with technical support and training guidance for software use, solve various problems in software use, and optimize software products through data management and feedback collection.

Job Responsibilities

Provide comprehensive customer service, including system configuration, to ensure customers can effectively use the company's software products;

Primarily provides technical support to customers via email, resolves software-related issues, and answers inquiries;

Assist department or project managers in coordinating project implementation to ensure that the entire project lifecycle meets customer service requirements;

Provide remote support, including troubleshooting, software updates, configuration modifications, etc., to resolve customer issues;

Provide training support to clients to help them understand and fully utilize the software's functions;

Responsible for data collection, import, and analysis, support the customer service process, and optimize products by combining customer feedback and usage patterns;

Ensure the daily smooth operation of software systems, monitor and promptly address issues, and minimize downtime to the greatest extent possible;

Efficiently and promptly resolve customer issues in accordance with company requirements and Service Level Agreements;

Provide value-added customer services such as account management and feedback collection to ensure customer satisfaction;

Participate in the creation and maintenance of documents and Knowledge Base to facilitate self-service for customers and improve support efficiency;

Maintain clear and professional communication with clients, and promptly synchronize relevant progress and information regarding issues or requirements;

Based on the client engagement status, provide feedback to the product development team to drive continuous product optimization;

For complex issues, coordinate and escalate to a higher-level support team or the corresponding internal department for resolution;

Monitor and report on individual and team performance indicators related to customer service;

Actively participate in the optimization of customer service processes and support tools to enhance the overall customer experience;

Deeply engage in the company's software products and related technologies, providing accurate and effective technical support;

Establish good partnerships with clients, understand their needs and preferences, and provide personalized support;

Collaborate with cross-functional teams such as sales, marketing, and product development to align customer service operations with the company's objectives;

Utilize excellent problem-solving skills to diagnose and resolve various technical issues encountered by clients;

Stay informed about product features, updates, and best practices in a timely manner to provide customers with the latest information;

Participate in continuous training and career development to enhance technical capabilities and customer service levels;

Ensure that all client-facing activities comply with the company's quality and professional standards;

Comply with company policies and industry regulations, and do a good job in data security and customer information protection;

Actively monitor customer engagement and system performance, anticipate and prevent potential issues;

As an Account Executive within the company, ensure that customer needs and feedback are valued and addressed.

Qualifications

Educational background: no explicit rigid requirements

Experience: Preference will be given to those with relevant customer service or technical support experience; those with team leadership or project management experience will be preferred

Language: Fluent English (listening, speaking, reading, and writing) is a prerequisite; additional proficiency in Japanese / Korean is preferred (salary can be adjusted)

Skills: Proficient in using Microsoft Office work suite (PowerPoint, Excel, Word, etc.); candidates with experience in using tools such as SQL, Jira, Salesforce, ServiceNow, etc. are preferred

Abilities: Possess strong critical thinking and problem-solving skills, emphasizing efficient execution and coordination; highly adaptable, able to effectively handle unexpected situations; excellent teamwork skills and outstanding interpersonal skills

Other: Willing and able to accept frequent business trips
